						##Managed instance groups & Load Balancers 


##Objective
- Learn how to build a self-healing private fleet of servers that are protected by an internal load blancer

##Key Concepts 

-Instance Template-
creating a template of a VM to ensure every server in y fleet is a perfect clone
of the origional 

-Managed Instance Group- (MIG)
an automation manager that ensures that i have a certan amout of VM's running to 
ensure security and gpu/cpu avaiablity 

-Health Cheack-
a protocol that sends a ping at a designated interval on the VM's specific port 
ton confirm if the VM is still alive, if no answer then assum it is broken and replace 

-Internal Load Balancer- (ILB)
the " Private front desk" provides a single permanat IP address for the entire fleet.
when other parts of the netwok want ot talk ot my servers they talk to the ILB and the ILB 
decides which heaslth VM should handle the request 

